laboratory_examinations.findings: Total testosterone: 1305 ng/dl (reference range: 300-1000 ng/dl); Free testosterone: 42 ng/dl (reference range: 5-20 ng/dl)
FSH: 8 mU/ml (reference range: 2-10 mU/ml); LH: 8 mU/ml (reference range: 2-10 mU/ml)
Estrone: 23 pg/ml (below the lower normal limit; reference range: 25-65 pg/ml)
Serum estradiol: undetectable (< 15 pg/ml; reference range: 0-30 pg/ml)
Osteocalcin: 132 ng/dl (reference range: 10-40 ng/dl), indicating increased rate of bone remodeling.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Osteocalcin significantly reduced to 88 ng/ml after 3 years of estrogen therapy.

laboratory_examinations.date: From age 17 yr and 1 month to 20 yr and 5 months
laboratory_examinations.findings: Lumbar spine: increased by 23%; Femoral neck: increased by 14%. Lumbar spine aBMD increased from -2.31 to -0.55, femoral neck aBMD from -0.46 to -0.44.

laboratory_examinations.date: From age 17 yr and 1 month to 20 yr and 5 months
laboratory_examinations.findings: BMAD at the spine increased from 0.120 to 0.136 g/cm³.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: BMAD at the femoral neck: from 0.156 to 0.147 g/cm³.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Total vBMD did not change significantly; vBMD decreased from 282 to 270 mg/cm³ during treatment.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: No significant changes in trabecular or cortical vBMD.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Cross-sectional area increased by 46%, from 247 to 360 mm².
